Sarkozy finds angry fishermen
Before taking off to the United States, Nicolas Sarkozy will give a ride to Britain.
Faced with the demonstration of resistance by fishermen who severely disturbed the entrances of several Breton and Norman ports last Monday, the President of the Republic decided to go last Tuesday to the port of Guilvinec, in the Finistère, to find his representatives there.
They promised to welcome him " with a constructive spirit " and hope that " come with concrete proposals ".
