What did they produce in the Zuschlag &amp; Co. invoice factory?
Very soon, on 8 October, the criminal proceedings against János Zuschlag and his accomplices will begin.
The politician and his accomplices are accused of committing significant damage fraud, in a business way, continuously and in an organized manner in addition to other crimes, including forgery of documents.
According to the Prosecutor ' s Office, the funds obtained in public procurement were used for their own purposes by justifying on many occasions the fulfilment of the tasks with false invoices.
The public funds and that of the municipalities - in their total of some 65 million HUF - partially stopped in the treasury of the organization Fiatal Baloldal and in part in the pocket of individuals.
The method, which was also made known by the researchers, was to justify the collection of funds obtained in public procurement with false invoices behind which there was no real execution, the different associations never fulfilled their obligations assumed.
According to the accusation, most bills were false.
For this they obtained the Talonaires in the Józsefvaros District market and the circular seals were manufactured in the city of Kiskunhalas.
And the question that on behalf of which company the falsified invoice was to be made was decided among others on that tour by the Balaton Superior Region where János Zuschlag sent to István Lados.
The latter confessed that for this purpose he had to choose hostels and restaurants.
He requested an invoice for his consumption and served as a model for the invoices that were presented, among others, in the contests of the Ministry of Youth and Sport Affairs, in the Ministry of Social and Labour Affairs, as well as in the City of Capital.
These invoices were mostly signed by István Sides and his accomplice András ..ri, who according to our information rather wrote the reports needed to obtain public grants.
During one of his "study trips" Sides chose a brewery.
According to two invoices issued in 2003 by Zuschlag and his accomplices, this gastronomy center provided food for a group of ninety people from the Pont Egyesület Biztos Association.
However - according to the center manager - so many people do not fit at once in that place.
Similarly, the bill issued in the summer of 2002 for the Jobb Jövőért Foundation - later called Együtt to Harmadik Évezredert - was full of formal and contextual errors.
For a hostel in the town of Badacsonytomaj had only three rooms and more than ten people could not stay there in one night, however the bill consisted of one hundred and thirty people.
But the very fancy bill manufacturers also exaggerated when they pointed to the Pigal Kft gastronomy centre. Because in the book hold of it - according to the information given to the Prosecutor's Office - there were no documents on behalf of Jobb Jövőért and Hoppá.
