In addition, the "shippers" made other mistakes as well, as in the case of a company where they put on the bill as an activity carried out the road transport to which - it was known during the prosecution's investigations - does not carry out the company founded as an investment consultant.
Equally due to formal differences - inadequate invoice format, false stamp - it is known that the invoices issued for Együtt to Harmadik Évezredert Alapítvány, for XXI. Századi Kulturális Egyesület and for Biztos Pont are false.
As in the case of Ravenna Bt. or the Kunfehertó Sports Camp, whose representatives refused to issue those invoices.
The falsifiers did not pay any attention to the fact that when the group of Fiatal Városért Egyesület ate there (2001) the HIB Kft. of Nyíregyháza was in the process of liquidation, so the person in charge of the liquidation process - according to our information - refused to have issued such a document.
They sent invoices consciously
Another group of false invoice manufacturers are those who were aware that they should issue fictitious invoices.
