We do everything we need to be ready to introduce the law as soon as they sign it - he added.
On the other hand, the heads of the banks who are in trouble and expect State aid may have the official limitation of their compensation, which the American argot simply calls gold parachute.
Only in certain cases will payments be limited, in addition limitations depend on the form of assistance of the Ministry of Finance.
Limitation means that if the ministry buys under a auction, an extra tax will be imposed on gold parachute unless the bank's failed chief retirees.
By buying the bad credits directly, the government will intervene aggressively to ensure that the bosses' compensations are not exaggerated.
In addition to the above, existing gold parachute contracts will not be changed, the limitations refer only to new contracts to stimulate participation in the programme.
This is the first case in American history that will be in effect a legal limitation for the general directors' incomes - said the Democrat Barney Frank, chairman of the Congress commission, responsible for financial services.
The State will also have the right to acquire shares from the banks participating in the programme, thus reducing the risk of taxpayers, since they may ultimately gain even with the transaction as soon as the economy is recovered and with it the bank.
According to the bill in the next five years, the president will have to submit to Congress a proposal on how to return to taxpayers the losses of the financial sector.
